bilingual.source: It is always in January or February.
Winter vacation is in February and March.
It is not always warm in February.
bilingual.target: 二月的天气并不总是暖和。

bilingual.source: February is the second month of the year.
bilingual.target: 二月是一年的第二个月。

bilingual.source: We will have an English party in February.
bilingual.target: 我们将在二月举办英语派对。

bilingual.source: Between February and May, hundreds of millions of fidget spinners were sold.
bilingual.target: 从二月到五月，售出了数亿个指尖陀螺。
二月通常是寒冷的月份。

list.abstract: february（英 [ˈfebruəri]，美 [ˈfebrueri]），英语单词，名词，为二月。例句为“We can see a new moon at the start of February.（我们可以在二月初看到新月。）”

yingyinNormal.en: No. All right, February, back of the issue. Did anybody speak with Salma's people yet?
yingyinNormal.zh: 不行 好了，言归正传，二月号背面，你们和萨尔玛联系过吗？

yingyinNormal.en: It's already February and I've only given two massages and they were both the worst tippers in the world.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在已经是二月，我只接到两个按摩客人，而且他们给小费都给得很吝啬。

yingyinNormal.en: Chinese New Year, also known as Lunar New Year, is celebrated throughout the world in late January or early February.
yingyinNormal.zh: 中国新年，又被称作农历新年，世界各地都在一月下旬或者二月上旬庆祝这个节日。

yingyinNormal.en: Guess who the university is sending to Switzerland to attend a conference and see the CERN super collider on February 14?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们猜学校要派谁去瑞士参加研讨会并参观欧洲核子研究委员会的超级对撞机，就在二月十四日？

yingyinNormal.en: Donald Stevens will join host Eleonor Gwah to discuss the death of his son, Army Captain Colter Stevens, who died in Afghanistan in February and was honored posthumously with the Silver Star.
yingyinNormal.zh: 唐纳德·斯蒂文斯，将与艾伦诺·戈瓦一起主持商议他儿子的死。陆军上尉考尔特·斯蒂文斯二月死于阿富汗，死后被授予了银星。

yingyinNormal.en: Rachel Karen Green, tell me there is gonna be a wedding. February 2nd.
yingyinNormal.zh: 告诉我你们会举行婚礼。二月二日。

yingyinNormal.en: Because you're innocent? No. I was moving product on February 26.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为你是无辜的吗？不，因为我是在26号干的。

yingyinNormal.en: February 15th, 2013, a meteor shining brighter than the sun streaks across Siberia.
yingyinNormal.zh: 2013年2月15日，一颗比太阳还要耀眼的流星划过西伯利亚。

yingyinNormal.en: There's no way the real estate agent could've seen me moving any product on February 25.
yingyinNormal.zh: 房产中介不可能看到我在25号搬运任何东西。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, she wasn't there. And she couldn't have seen it on February 25 because it wasn't happening.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没错，她当时不在那里，她也不可能在25号看到，因为那时并没有那回事。

yingyinNormal.en: We only mentioned Mr. Bishop's February 26 location once, and that was in the meeting with your firm.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们唯一提过毕夏普先生26号的下落，就是在你的律所开会的时候。

yingyinNormal.en: In China, the New Year can start from like, the middle of January than to the end of February. And this lunar cycle repeats itself every 12 years.
yingyinNormal.zh: 中国的春节那天会在是1月中旬到2月底其间的一天。这种农历的循环每12年重复一次。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2015-2022年全国卷高考试卷，包括阅读、完形、单选、填空、听力、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Wang Shu, a 49-year-old Chinese architect, won the 2012 Pritzker Architecture Prize on <highlight>February</highlight> 28.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 2月28日，49岁的中国建筑师王澍获得了2012年普利兹克建筑奖。
